1️⃣ Definitions 📜
1.1. "Contributor" 🧑‍💻
Each individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to, or owns Covered Software.

1.2. "Contributor Version" 🔄
The combination of others’ Contributions used by a Contributor, including that Contributor’s own.

1.3. "Contribution" 💡
Covered Software from a particular Contributor.

1.4. "Covered Software" 📁
Source Code, Executable Form, and Modifications of that Source Code with the notice in Exhibit A.

1.5. "Incompatible With Secondary Licenses" 🚫
Covered Software with restrictions as detailed in Exhibit B.

1.6. "Executable Form" 🖥️
The version of the work other than Source Code Form.

1.7. "Larger Work" 🌍
A combination of Covered Software with other material that isn't Covered Software.

1.8. "License" 📜
This document!

1.9. "Licensable" 🏷️
The right to grant all rights conveyed by this License.

1.10. "Modifications" 🔧
Changes, additions, or deletions to the Covered Software.

1.11. "Patent Claims" 🔒
Patent claims that would be infringed by using the Contributions unless granted by this License.

1.12. "Secondary License" 💼
Specific licenses like the GNU licenses that may apply under certain conditions.

1.13. "Source Code Form" 💻
The preferred format for making modifications.

1.14. "You" (or "Your") 👤
Anyone using this License.

